{{see|Bludger}}

==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{AU}} {{slang}} A person who avoids working , or who does not do their share of work, a [[loafer]], a [[hanger on]], one who does not [[pull one's weight|pull their weight]]
# {{AU}} {{slang}} {{obsolete}} A man living off the earnings of a [[harlot]].  (Reference: Sidney J. Baker, ''The Australian Language'', second edition, 1966, chapter VI section 3, page 129, mentioning an 1882 record of this usage,)
====Derived terms====
*[[dole bludger]] - A person who lives off the [[dole]] ([[welfare]])

